$lang['The hexadecimal system is a base 16 number notation, while the decimal system is a base 10 number notation. In other words, the hexadecimal system uses 16 symbols to represent numbers, while the decimal system uses 10 symbols. This expansion also allows for a higher information density-hexadecimal digits can represent twice as many values as decimal digits.'] = 'Suqta chunkayuq llikaqa 16 sapsi yupay qillqam, chunkayuq llikataq 10 sapsi yupay qillqam. Huk rimaypiqa, suqta chunkayuq sistemaqa 16 siñalkunatam llamk&#39;achin yupaykunata rikuchinapaq, chunkayuq sistemataq 10 chikukunata llamk&#39;achin. Kay mastariyqa aswan hatun willay densidadta saqillantaq-suqta chunkayuq yupaykuna iskay kuti aswan chanikunata chunkayuq yupaykunamanta rikuchiyta atinku.';
