$lang['When converting hexadecimal to decimal, the first step is to divide the hex number by 16. This will give you the base number. The second step is to divide each digit of the hex number by 16 and write down the results. Finally, add up all of the numbers that were just calculated.'] = 'Hexadecimalta chunkayuqman tikraspaqa, ñawpaq ruwayqa hexadecimal yupayta 16. Kaywanqa base yupayta qusunki. Iskay kaq ruwayqa, hex yupaypa sapa yupayninta 16man rakispa, chaymanta ruwasqakunata qillqana. Tukuchanapaqtaq, chayraq yupasqa llapa yupaykunata huñuy.';
$lang['For example, if someone wants to convert 9F7A to decimal, they would first divide 9F7A by 16 which equals 6051. Then they would divide each digit of 6051 by 16 which equals 381. Lastly, they would add up 381 + 381 + 381 which equals 1144. Therefore, 9F7A in decimal is equal to 1144'] = 'Ejemplopaq, sichus pipas 9F7Ata decimalman tikrayta munanman chayqa, ñawpaqtaqa 9F7Ata 16wan rakinmanku chaymi 6051wan tupan, chaymantataq 6051pa sapa dígitonta rakinmanku 16wan chaymi tupan 381. Tukuyninpiqa huñunkumanmi 381 + 381 + 381ta chaymi kaqlla 1144. Chayraykum chunkayuqpi 9F7A 1144wan kaqlla';
$lang['How do you convert a Decimal to a Hexadecimal?'] = '¿Imaynatataq Decimalta Hexadecimalman tikranki?';
$lang['Converting decimal to hexadecimal is a simple process, and can be done with a calculator or online converter. In order to convert the number, divide it by 16 and take the remainder. This remainder will then correspond to a hexadecimal digit. For example, if you have the decimal number 234, divide it by 16 and take the remainder: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Therefore, in hexadecimal notation, this number would be written as “E2”.'] = 'Chunka chunkayuq yupayta suqta chunkayuqman tikrayqa sasan ruwaymi, chaymanta yupaywan utaq internetpi tikraqwan ruwakunman. Yupayta tikranapaqqa 16man rakispa puchuqninta hapiy. Chaymantaqa kay puchuqqa suqta chunkayuq yupaywanmi tupanqa. Ejemplopaq, 234 chunkayuq yupayniyuq kaspaqa 16man rakispa puchuqninta hapiy: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Chayraykum suqta chunkayuq yupaypiqa kay yupayqa “E2” nispa qillqasqa kanman.';
$lang['There are many tools available online that can help with converting between decimal and hexadecimal numbers. Additionally, most calculators have a built-in function that will allow you to do this conversion very easily. With just a few clicks of the mouse or taps on the keyboard, you’ll be able to change any decimal value into its corresponding hexadecimal equivalent!'] = 'Internetpiqa achka yanapakuykunam kachkan, chaykunam yanapanman chunkayuq hinaspa suqta chunkayuq yupaykunata tikraypi. Chaymanta, aswan yupaqkuna huk ruwasqa ruwanayuq kanku chaymanta kay tikrayta ancha facil ruwayta atikunki. ¡Aswan pisi ñit&#39;iyllawan utaq teclado kaqpi ñit&#39;iyllawan, mayqin chunkayuq chaniyuqtapas tupaqnin hexadecimal kaqninman tikrayta atikunki!';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Hexadecimal over a Decimal?'] = '¿Ima allinkunan kanman Hexadecimal nisqawan Decimal nisqawan?';
$lang['The hexadecimal, or base-16, system was designed to emulate some of the same properties as the decimal system. In other words, it was created to make things easier for us humans. The number 423 has 16 digits instead of 10 digits available in a decimal system. This is because hexadecimal uses a base of 16 symbols instead of 10. After F, the order begins again with 0 and so on and so forth until we get to 15 which is notated as F.'] = 'Hexadecimal icha base-16 nisqa sistemaqa chunkayuq sistema nisqawan wakin kikin propiedades nisqakunata qatipanapaqmi ruwasqa karqan. Huk rimaypiqa, ñuqanchik runakunapaq imapas mana sasachakunanpaqmi unanchasqa karqa. 423 yupayqa 16 yupayniyuqmi, chunka yupayniyuq sistemapi 10 yupayniyuqmantaqa. Kayqa kanman, hexadecimal 10pa rantinpi 16 siñalkunayuq baseta llamkachisqanraykum, F nisqamanta qipamanqa, ordenqa yapamantam 0wan qallarin hinaspa hukkunawanpas 15man chayananchikkama chaymi F nispa notasqa kachkan.';
$lang['Hexadecimal encoding reduces the number of digits by a factor of eight when compared to the decimal system. Additionally, hexadecimal numbers have an information density that is twice as high as decimal numbers do. So, why should you bother learning this funky little numbering scheme? Because it can make your life easier! When working with digital systems or data transmission, using hex will save you time and energy when decoding cryptic messages or data streams.'] = 'Hexadecimal codificación nisqawanmi chunka yupayta pusaq factorwan pisiyachin, chunkayuq sistemawan tupachisqa. Chaymantapas, suqta chunkayuq yupaykunaqa chunkayuq yupaykunamanta iskay kuti aswan hatun willay densidadniyuqmi. Hinaptinqa, ¿imaraykutaq kay funky uchuy esquema de numeración yachayta llakikunayki tiyan? ¡Imaraykuchus kawsayniykita aswan facilta ruwanman! Sistemas digitales kaqwan utaq willaykunata apachiywan llamk&#39;achkaspa, hex llamk&#39;achiyta pachata chaymanta kallpata waqaychanki mayk&#39;aq criptico willakuykunata utaq willay mayukunata descodificanki.';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Decimal over a Hexadecimal?'] = '¿Ima allinkunan kanman Decimal nisqawan Hexadecimal nisqawan llamk’ayqa?';
$lang['When it comes to binary coding, Hexadecimal is more efficient because it reduces 8 digits to 2. Additionally, Hex provides a greater degree of information density and higher accuracy in numbers than binary does. This is due to the fact that Hex uses 16 symbols instead of just two like binary. Because of this increased efficiency, Hexadecimal is often used when binary coding in computing and digital electronics as well as for computer science applications.'] = 'Iskayniyuq codificación nisqamanta rimaspaqa, Hexadecimal nisqa aswan allinmi, 8 digitokunata 2 nisqaman pisiyachisqanrayku, chaymantapas, Hex nisqa aswan hatun grado de información densidad nisqatam qun, yupaykunapipas aswan chiqap kaynintam qun iskayniyuqmantaqa. Kayqa Hex 16 siñalkunata iskayniyuq hina iskaylla llamk&#39;achisqanraykum. Kay yapasqa allin ruwayrayku, Hexadecimal sapa kuti llamk&#39;achisqa iskay codificación kaqpi computadora kaqpi chaymanta digital electrónica kaqpi chaymanta computadora ciencia kaqpaq llamk&#39;achinapaq.';
$lang['In addition, Hexadecimal takes up less space than decimal. With only two digits instead of 8 binary digits, Hex numbers represent large numbers much more concisely. This can be very helpful when working with computer systems, as there is less chance for mistakes when typing in hex codes compared to decimal codes which have so many decimal points all over the place!'] = 'Chaymantapas, Hexadecimalqa chunkayuqmantaqa pisi espaciotam hapin. Iskay yupayniyuqlla 8 iskay yupayniyuq yupaykunamantaqa, Hex yupaykunaqa hatun yupaykunatam aswan pisi rimayllapi rikuchin. Kayqa ancha yanapakuq kanman computadora sistemakunawan llamk&#39;achkaspa, imaynachus aswan pisi chansa pantaypaq kan hex códigokunapi qillqachkaspa chunkayuq códigokunawan tupachisqa mayqinkunachus ancha achka chunkayuq puntokuna tukuy kitipi kanku!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Hexadecimal?'] = '¿Imataq Hexadecimal nisqawan rikuchinapaq chanikunap llikan?';
$lang['A hexadecimal number is a number that uses 16 digits instead of the 10 digits we use in the decimal system. This number system is called base-16, and it helps us to emulate the properties of our familiar decimal system. In hexadecimal, each digit represents a power of 16. The numbers 0 through 9 represent the powers of 1 through 10, while A through F represent the powers of 11 through 15.'] = 'Suqta chunkayuq yupay nisqaqa chunkayuq llikap llamk&#39;achisqan 10 yupayniyuq yupaymi , 16 yupayniyuq yupaymi. Kay yupay sistemaqa base-16 sutiyuqmi, chaymi yanapawanchik riqsisqa chunkayuq sistemanchikpa propiedades nisqakunata qatipanapaq. Hexadecimal nisqapiqa sapa yupaymi 16 kallpata rikuchin, 0manta 9kama yupaykunaqa 1manta 10kama atiykunatan rikuchin, Amanta Fkamataq 11manta 15kama atiykunata rikuchin.';
$lang['Just like in decimal, after 16 symbols have been used in Hexadecimal, the order of numbers starts over again at zero. So, hexadecimal 10 is equal to decimal 16, and hexadecimal 11 is equal to decimal 17. And so on!'] = 'Chunkayuqpi hina, Hexadecimal nisqapi 16 chimpukuna llamk&#39;achisqa kaptin, yupaykunap ordenninqa musuqmanta qallarikun cero nisqapi. Hinaptinqa, suqta chunkayuq 10 chunkayuq 16 yupaywan kaqlla, suqta chunkayuq 11taq chunkayuq 17. ¡Hinallataq!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Decimal?'] = '¿Imataq Decimal nisqawan rikuchinapaq chanikunap llikan?';
$lang['The Decimal system starts with 10 and goes up to 15. This means that the range of values that can be represented by a decimal number is from 0-9, followed by A-F (10-15).'] = 'Sistema Decimal nisqa 10 nisqawan qallarin, 15kamataqmi rin, chaymi niyta munan, chunkayuq yupaywan rikuchiy atikuq chanikunap llikanqa 0-9 nisqamanta, chaymantataq AF (10-15) nisqamanta.';
$lang['How do you decode Hexadecimal?'] = '¿Imaynatataq Hexadecimalta descodificanki?';
$lang['When it comes to decoding Hexadecimal, there are a few things you need to know. First, just like the decimal system, the hexadecimal system has 10 symbols (0-9) that represent numbers. However, in hexadecimal, these digits have values that are twice as large as their counterparts in the decimal system. So, while the number “10” is represented by the symbol “A” in hexadecimal, it would be equal to “10” in the decimal system.'] = 'Hexadecimal descodificaymanta rimaspaqa, kanmi iskay kimsa imakuna yachanaykipaq. Ñawpaqtaqa, chunkayuq sistema hina, suqta chunkayuq sistemaqa 10 siñalniyuqmi (0-9) yupaykunata riqsichiq. Ichaqa suqta chunkayuqpi, kay yupaykunaqa iskay kuti aswan hatun chaniyuqmi, chunkayuq llikapi kaqninkunamantaqa. Chaymi, “10” yupayqa hexadecimal nisqapi “A” nisqawan rikuchisqa kaptinpas, chunkayuq sistemapiqa “10” nisqawanmi kaqlla kanman.';
$lang['Similarly, after reaching 9 in Hexadecimal (represented by “F”), we start counting again at 10 (“10”). This pattern continues until we reach 15 (“1F”), at which point we reset back to 0 and begin counting again at 16 (“20”). This might sound confusing at first, but with a little practice, it will become second nature!'] = 'Chaynallataqmi, Hexadecimal nisqapi 9 nisqaman chayaspa (“F” nisqawan riqsichisqa), 10 (“10”) nisqamanta yapamanta yupayta qallarinchik. Kay patrónqa 15 (“1F”) nisqaman chayananchikkamam purin, chaypim 0 nisqaman kutiykunchik hinaspam 16 (“20”) nisqaman yapamanta yupayta qallaykunchik. Kayqa qallariypiqa pantasqa hinam rikchakunman, ichaqa pisillata practicaspaqa segunda naturalezamanmi tikrakunqa!';
