$lang['Hexadecimal is a way of representing binary data in human-readable form. It was developed in the 19th century to allow computers to store large amounts of information.'] = 'Hexadecimal nisqaqa iskayniyuq willayta runap ñawirinapaq hina rikuchiyninmi. Chaytaqa XIX siglopin ruwarqanku, chhaynapi computadorakunapi askha willakuykunata waqaychanankupaq.';
$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Chunka chunkayuq chanikunata iskayniyuq chanikunapura tikranaykipaqqa suqta chunkayuq llamk&#39;achiyta atinki. Ahinataq, 10011011001010 suqta chunkayuqman tikrayqa 0x4F nisqatam qunman. Kayqa niyta munan, 4F chaniqa 100110110010110 iskay yupayta riqsichin.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Yupay yachaypi , kumpi yachaypipas suqta chunkayuq (16 kaq sapsi, icha hexagona kaqpas) nisqaqa 16 radix icha sapsiyuq , 16. Chunka suqtayuq sapaq simp&#39;ikunatam llamk&#39;achin, aswan achka kuti 0–9 simp&#39;akunata ceromanta isqunkama chanikunata rikuchinapaq, hinaspa A, B, C, D, E, F (utaq hukmanta a–f) chunkamanta chunka pichqayuqkama chaninchasqakunata qawachinapaq. Ejemplopaq, suqta chunkayuq yupay 2AF3 kaqlla, chunkayuqpi, (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , utaq 10.995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Sapa suqta chunkayuq yupayqa tawa iskayniyuq yupaykunatam (bits) rikuchin (&quot;nibble&quot; nisqapas), suqta chunkayuq notacionpa ñawpaq llamk&#39;ayninqa iskayniyuq codificasqa chanikunap runap allin rikuchiynin hinam, yupaypi, digital electrónica nisqapipas. Ejemplopaq, byte chanikuna 0manta 255kama (chunkayuq) kanman ichaqa aswan allinta iskay suqta chunkayuq yupay hina rikuchisqa kanman 00manta FFkama. Hexadecimal nisqaqa computadorap yuyarina direccionninkunata rikuchinapaqmi llamk&#39;achinku.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex nisqaqa Hexadecimal nisqap pisichasqanmi, -16 nisqap sapsi ruranapi sayasqa, computadorakunaman kamachiykuna imayna rikuchisqa kasqanmanta pisiyachinapaq. Kay 16 siñal yupay sistemaqa 8 bits iskayniyuq yupayta hark&#39;anapaq ruwasqa karqan, chayrayku willaykunata computadorakunaman mana kallpachakuywan codificayta atikun. Iskay chikan hexagonal yupaykunata llamk&#39;achispa imprimiyta chaymanta qillqayta atikunman sapa hex yupaywan huk nibble utaq ichapas 4-bits formato rikuchiq.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Kay yupay sistemaqa 16 siñalkunatam llamk&#39;achin, chaykunam 0-9 utaq AF nisqamanta huk llimp&#39;ipi rikuchisqa. 0–9 isqunkama yupaykunata riqsichin maypichus AF yupaywan 10–15 yupaywan riqsichikun. Wak kimsa laya yupay sistemakunawan tupachisqaqa, suqta chunkayuq yupay sistemaqa aswan allinpaqmi qhawarikun.';
